From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000029 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 01:40:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] leds: steelhead-avr: make the frame bin_attr readable

nexusqd renders the LED ring exclusively through the frame bin_attr,
which was write-only — so the system had NO readable source of the ring
state: the per-LED multicolor classdev brightness files only reflect
what was set through the classdev API and stay 0 under nexusqd. The
nq-healthd monitor fingerprinted those brightness files and therefore
reported a permanently frozen ring (led_sum=0/led_stall CRIT on every
capture; root-caused 2026-07-03).

Add a read callback returning the last committed frame from the
driver's own state under io_lock, and open the attr up to 0644. The
health monitor fingerprints this (with a brightness fallback for older
kernels); reading is also generally useful for debugging the ring.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
--- a/drivers/leds/leds-steelhead-avr.c
+++ b/drivers/leds/leds-steelhead-avr.c
@@ -260,7 +260,39 @@
 	mutex_unlock(&a->io_lock);
 	return ret ? ret : (ssize_t)count;
 }
-static BIN_ATTR(frame, 0200, NULL, frame_write, AVR_RING_LEDS * 3);
+static ssize_t frame_read(struct file *fp, struct kobject *kobj,
+			  struct bin_attribute *attr, char *buf,
+			  loff_t off, size_t count)
+{
+	struct device *dev = kobj_to_dev(kobj);
+	struct avr_dev *a = i2c_get_clientdata(to_i2c_client(dev));
+	u8 fbuf[AVR_RING_LEDS * 3];
+	int i;
+
+	/*
+	 * Expose the last committed frame. nexusqd renders exclusively through
+	 * this bin_attr, so with it write-only there was NO readable source of
+	 * ring state at all — the per-LED classdev brightness files only track
+	 * what was set through the classdev API and stay 0 under nexusqd,
+	 * which made nq-healthd's frame fingerprint report a permanently
+	 * frozen ring (false CRIT on every capture, found 2026-07-03).
+	 */
+	mutex_lock(&a->io_lock);
+	for (i = 0; i < AVR_RING_LEDS; i++) {
+		fbuf[i*3 + 0] = a->ring[i].r;
+		fbuf[i*3 + 1] = a->ring[i].g;
+		fbuf[i*3 + 2] = a->ring[i].b;
+	}
+	mutex_unlock(&a->io_lock);
+
+	if (off >= sizeof(fbuf))
+		return 0;
+	if (count > sizeof(fbuf) - off)
+		count = sizeof(fbuf) - off;
+	memcpy(buf, fbuf + off, count);
+	return count;
+}
+static BIN_ATTR(frame, 0644, frame_read, frame_write, AVR_RING_LEDS * 3);
 
 static ssize_t commit_mode_show(struct device *dev,
 				struct device_attribute *attr, char *buf)
